Class FloatScatterSet

    @Generated(date="2015-05-05T11:00:03+0200",
           value="KTypeScatterSet.java")
public class FloatScatterSet
extends FloatHashSet
    Same as FloatHashSet but does not implement per-instance key mixing strategy and uses a simpler (faster) bit distribution function.

    Note: read about important differences between hash and scatter sets.

      • hashKey

        protected int hashKey(float key)
        Description copied from class: FloatHashSet
        Returns a hash code for the given key. The default implementation mixes the hash of the key with FloatHashSet.keyMixer to differentiate hash order of keys between hash containers. Helps alleviate problems resulting from linear conflict resolution in open addressing. The output from this function should evenly distribute keys across the entire integer range.
        Overrides:
        hashKey in class FloatHashSet
